# Chapter 85: Electrical Machinery and Equipment; Sound Recorders and Reproducers; Television Recorders and Reproducers

CHAPTER_85_NOTES = """
CHAPTER 85 - ELECTRICAL MACHINERY AND EQUIPMENT AND PARTS THEREOF; SOUND RECORDERS AND REPRODUCERS, TELEVISION IMAGE AND SOUND RECORDERS AND REPRODUCERS, AND PARTS AND ACCESSORIES OF SUCH ARTICLES

Notes:
1. This chapter does NOT cover:
   (a) Electrically warmed blankets, bed pads, foot-muffs, clothing, footwear, ear pads, or other articles worn on person;
   (b) Articles of glass (heading 7011);
   (c) Machines and apparatus (heading 8486);
   (d) Vacuum apparatus for medical, surgical, dental, or veterinary sciences (heading 9018);
   (e) Electrically heated furniture (chapter 94).

2. Headings 8501-8504 do NOT apply to goods of heading 8511, 8512, 8540, 8541, or 8542. HOWEVER: metal tank mercury arc rectifiers remain in heading 8504.

3. "Electric accumulators" (heading 8507) includes those with ancillary components for storing and supplying energy or protection (electrical connectors, temperature control devices, circuit protection devices). May include portion of protective housing.

4. Heading 8509 covers ONLY electromechanical machines commonly used for domestic purposes:
   (a) Floor polishers, food grinders and mixers, fruit or vegetable juice extractors, of any weight;
   (b) Other machines ≤20 kg (exclusive of extra interchangeable parts or detachable auxiliary devices).
   EXCLUDES: fans, ventilating or recycling hoods with fan (heading 8414), centrifugal clothes dryers (heading 8421), dishwashing machines (heading 8422), household washing machines (heading 8450), ironing machines (heading 8420 or 8451), sewing machines (heading 8452), electric scissors (heading 8467), electrothermic appliances (heading 8516).

5. "Smartphones" (heading 8517) = cellular network telephones with mobile operating system for ADP machine functions (downloading and running multiple applications simultaneously, including third-party applications), whether or not integrating digital cameras, navigational aid systems, etc.

6. For heading 8523:
   (a) "Solid-state non-volatile storage devices" (e.g., flash memory cards) = storage devices with connecting socket, comprising one or more flash memories (FLASH E²PROM) as integrated circuits on printed circuit board. May include controller IC and discrete passive components;
   (b) "Smart cards" = cards with embedded electronic integrated circuits (microprocessor, RAM, or ROM) as chips. May contain contacts, magnetic stripe, or embedded antenna, but NO other active or passive circuit elements.

7. "Flat panel display modules" (heading 8524) = devices for information display equipped with at least a display screen, designed for incorporation into articles of other headings before use. Display screens may be flat, curved, flexible, foldable, or stretchable. May incorporate elements for receiving video signals and allocating to pixels. Does NOT include modules with video signal conversion components (scaler IC, decoder IC, application processor) or modules that have assumed character of other heading goods.
   Heading 8524 takes PRECEDENCE over any other tariff heading.

8. "Printed circuits" (heading 8534) = circuits obtained by forming on insulating base (by printing, embossing, plating-up, etching, or film circuit technique) conductor elements, contacts, or other printed components (inductances, resistors, capacitors) alone or interconnected according to pre-established pattern. EXCLUDES elements that can produce, rectify, modulate, or amplify electrical signal (semiconductor elements). Does NOT cover circuits combined with elements other than those from printing process, nor individual discrete resistors, capacitors, or inductances. May be fitted with non-printed connecting elements.
   Thin- or thick-film circuits with passive and active elements from same process → heading 8542.

9. "Connectors for optical fibres, optical fibre bundles or cables" (heading 8536) = connectors that simply mechanically align optical fibres end to end in digital line system. No other function (no amplification, regeneration, or signal modification).

10. Heading 8537 does NOT include cordless infrared devices for remote control of television receivers or other electrical equipment (heading 8543).

11. "Light-emitting diode (LED) light sources" (heading 8539):
    (a) "LED modules" = electrical light sources based on LEDs in electrical circuits, containing further elements (electrical, mechanical, thermal, optical). Also contain discrete active or passive elements, or heading 8536 or 8542 articles for power supply or control. Do NOT have cap for easy installation or replacement in luminaire;
    (b) "LED lamps" = electrical light sources containing one or more LED modules plus further elements. HAVE cap for easy installation or replacement in luminaire and ensuring mechanical and electrical contact.

12. For headings 8541 and 8542:
    (a)(i) "Semiconductor devices" = devices whose operation depends on resistivity variations on electric field application, or semiconductor-based transducers.
    
    "Semiconductor-based transducers" = semiconductor-based sensors, actuators, resonators, and oscillators that perform intrinsic function and convert physical or chemical phenomena to electrical signal or vice versa. Elements are indivisibly combined.
    
    Definitions:
    - "Semiconductor-based" = built on semiconductor substrate, made of semiconductor materials, or manufactured by semiconductor technology where semiconductor plays critical role;
    - "Physical or chemical phenomena" = pressure, acoustic waves, acceleration, vibration, movement, orientation, strain, magnetic field strength, electric field strength, light, radioactivity, humidity, flow, chemical concentration;
    - "Semiconductor-based sensor" = detects physical or chemical quantities and converts to electric signals;
    - "Semiconductor-based actuator" = converts electric signals into physical movement;
    - "Semiconductor-based resonator" = generates mechanical or electrical oscillation of predefined frequency in response to external input;
    - "Semiconductor-based oscillator" = generates mechanical or electrical oscillation of predefined frequency.
    
    (a)(ii) "Light-emitting diodes (LED)" = semiconductor devices converting electrical energy to visible, infra-red, or ultra-violet rays, whether or not electrically connected or combined with protective diodes. LEDs of heading 8541 do NOT incorporate elements for power supply or control;

    (b) "Electronic integrated circuits":
        (i) Monolithic integrated circuits = circuit elements (diodes, transistors, resistors, capacitors, inductances) created in mass and on surface of semiconductor or compound semiconductor material, inseparably associated;
        (ii) Hybrid integrated circuits = passive elements (thin- or thick-film technology) + active elements (semiconductor technology) combined indivisibly by interconnections on single insulating substrate (glass, ceramic). May include discrete components;
        (iii) Multichip integrated circuits = two or more interconnected monolithic ICs combined indivisibly, with or without insulating substrates, with or without leadframes, but no other active or passive circuit elements;
        (iv) Multi-component integrated circuits (MCOs) = combination of one or more monolithic, hybrid, or multichip ICs with at least one of: silicon-based sensors, actuators, oscillators, resonators, or combinations; or components performing heading 8532, 8533, 8541 functions, or inductors (heading 8504), formed indivisibly into single body for PCB assembly.

    Headings 8541 and 8542 take PRECEDENCE over any other tariff heading, EXCEPT heading 8523 which might cover them by function reference.

Subheading Notes:
1. Subheading 8525.81: high-speed television cameras, digital cameras, video camera recorders with: writing speed >0.5 mm/μs, time resolution ≤50 ns, or frame rate >225,000 fps.
2. Subheading 8525.82: radiation-hardened or radiation-tolerant cameras designed for high-radiation environment, withstanding total radiation dose ≥50×10³ Gy (5×10⁶ RAD silicon).
3. Subheading 8525.83: night vision cameras using photocathode to convert light to electrons for amplification and visible image. EXCLUDES thermal imaging cameras.
4. Subheading 8527.12: cassette players with built-in amplifier, without built-in loudspeaker, no external power needed, dimensions ≤170 mm × 100 mm × 45 mm.
5. Subheadings 8549.11-8549.19: "spent primary cells, spent primary batteries and spent electric accumulators" = those unusable because of breakage, cutting-up, wear, or other reasons, nor capable of being recharged.

Additional U.S. Notes:
1. For headings 8501 and 8503: 746 W = 1 hp.
2. "Toasters" (subheading 8516.72) includes toaster-ovens designed essentially for toasting bread but can also bake small items.
3. "Transceivers" (headings 8517 and 8525) = combinations of radio transmitting and receiving equipment in common housing, using common circuit components for both, NOT capable of simultaneously receiving and transmitting.
"""

